arez.component

Class ComponentState

  • java.lang.Object
    • arez.component.ComponentState

  • public final class ComponentState
extends Object
    This class is used in generated code to manage the state of the component. This is centralized here so that it is easier for GWT to optimize it either by sharing the methods implementation or inlining as appropriate.

      • COMPONENT_CONSTRUCTED

        public static final byte COMPONENT_CONSTRUCTED
        The reactive elements have been created (i.e. the ObservableValue, Observer, ComputedValue etc.). The PostConstruct has NOT been invoked nor has the Component been instantiated. This means the component is ready to be interacted with in a PostConstruct method but has not been fully constructed.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • COMPONENT_COMPLETE

        public static final byte COMPONENT_COMPLETE
        The PostConstruct method has been invoked and the Component has been instantiated. Observers have been scheduled but the scheduler has not been triggered.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
